<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN SHOOTING INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 21-year-old man who allegedly fired a gun in an apartment complex during a 
fight with a female acquaintance was arrested Monday morning and released on 
bail in the afternoon, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Kilven of Simi Valley was held on suspicion of discharging a firearm in a 
grossly negligent manner, carrying a partly concealed weapon and carrying a 
loaded weapon, said Sgt. Larry Twichell of the Simi Valley Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Kilven was released from the Ventura County Jail about 1:30 p.m. Monday on 
$5,000 bail, said Sgt. Cole McDaniel of the Ventura County Sheriff's 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrived at the 5500 block of Cochran Street about 2:45 a.m. Monday after 
receiving several 911 calls about the shots, and they found Kilven walking in 
the area, Twichell said. KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
