<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPERATION RESCUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re: "Anti-Abortion Protesters Get Terms Up to 215 Days," (Metro, July 17) 
</P>
<P>
Can anyone seriously doubt that we are witnessing judicial tyranny? Who in his 
right mind would not be aghast at a seven-month jail term for misdemeanor 
trespassing? 
</P>
<P>
It seems the only minority that can be persecuted with impunity are vocal 
Christians. 
</P>
<P>
In recent months, jail terms for first- offense trespassers have become common. 
This is a violation of both justice and common sense. 
</P>
<P>
The fact that there isn't a national uproar over the unjust and tyrannical 
oppression of these conscientious people tells me that as a nation we don't 
want to face the reality of abortion. 
</P>
<P>
Those who call our attention to this national disgrace deserve the same respect 
and legal protection that the civil rights protesters gained in the '60s. 
</P>
<P>
PETER WARNER 
</P>
<P>
Gardena 
</P>
</TEXT>
