</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles (Red) Barrett, who holds the major league record for the fewest pitches 
in a nine-inning game, died at his home in Wilson, N.C., Saturday after a long 
illness. He was 75. Barrett, while pitching for the Boston Braves in 1944, 
faced 27 batters and threw only 58 pitches in a 2-0 victory over the Cincinnati 
Reds. 
</P>
