<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Broad Inc.: The Los Angeles-based financial services company reported net 
income of $10.7 million for its third quarter ended June 30, up 17% from $9.2 
million a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Net operating income (before net realized investment losses) rose 63% in the 
quarter to $15.8 million from $9.6 million. Chief Executive Eli Broad 
attributed the operating gain to a higher level of assets under management 
following the firm's acquisition of the core financial services businesses of 
Integrated Resources in January. However, the company also is experiencing a 
modestly higher level of net realized investment losses than anticipated 
earlier, he said. 
</P>
