<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS' HENLEY COLLAPSES IN LOCKER ROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ram cornerback Darryl Henley collapsed in the team's locker room at UC Irvine 
Monday evening and was taken to a hospital, where he was treated for what the 
Rams described as "exhaustion and dehydration." 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Tustin Health Care Medical Center would say only that Henley's 
condition was stable. 
</P>
<P>
The second-year cornerback from UCLA collapsed on the trainer's table at 6:20 
p.m., about 90 minutes after Monday's afternoon practice ended. He was treated 
at the scene by paramedics. 
</P>
<P>
"He was cramping up in the locker room," said linebacker Paul Butcher, an 
eyewitness. "He was hyperventilating a little bit." 
</P>
<P>
The Rams later released a statement, which read, in part: "Henley's condition 
has been stabilized and he is currently undergoing additional precautionary 
tests. He will be released later this evening and return to the Rams training 
facility at UC Irvine." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FOOTBALL PLAYERS -- HEALTH; LOS ANGELES RAMS (FOOTBALL TEAM); HENLEY, DARRYL 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
