<TEXT>
<P>
Billy Martin's widow has sued the man allegedly behind the wheel of the pickup 
truck in which the former New York Yankee manager was killed in a Christmas 
night accident. 
</P>
<P>
William Reedy, the owner of a Detroit bar, was negligent when he failed to 
negotiate a curve outside Martin's rural Upstate New York home and lost control 
of the truck, which slid down a ditch and into a culvert, Jill Martin's lawsuit 
charged. 
</P>
<P>
Martin, 61, a passenger in the truck, suffered fatal neck and head injuries in 
the crash. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said a test administered to the 53-year-old Reedy soon after the 
accident indicated that he was legally drunk. 
</P>
