<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Rates Mixed: The Treasury sold $9.3 billion of new three-month bills at 
an average discount rate of 7.50%, up from 7.49% last week. Another $9.2 
billion in new six-month bills was sold at an average discount rate of 7.37%, 
down from 7.40% last week. 
</P>
<P>
The three-month bill rate was the highest since the 7.62% rate of July 16. The 
six-month bill rate was the lowest since averaging 7.30% last Dec. 4. The new 
discount rates understate the actual return to investors -- 7.75% for 
three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,810.40 and 7.76% for a 
six-month bill selling for $9,627.40. The discount rate reflects the price 
discount received when government securities are purchased at less than face 
value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
