<TEXT>
<P>
Ball Announces Acquisition: Ball Corp. has acquired 33 metal-packaging plants 
in Europe from Continental Can Co., giving the Muncie, Ind.-based business a 
launching pad for the rapidly expanding European market, company officials 
said. Continental will receive $625 million in cash and $400 million in stock, 
giving it a 29% stake in Ball. Ball also said it would pay $65 million in cash 
to purchase the remaining 50% in Ball-InCon Glass Packaging Corp. from its 
partner, Holland-American Investment Corp. 
</P>
