<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLANE WRECKS YIELD REMAINS OF 2 PILOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wreckage of two small private planes -- one missing for more than three 
years -- and the remains of their pilots have been found in mountains near the 
Owens Valley, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
A hiker near Hart Lake, 37 miles southeast of Bishop, discovered the skeletal 
remains of a pilot whose single-engine Cessna 172 disappeared in June, 1987, 
said Inyo County sheriff's deputies. The name of the pilot was withheld pending 
notification of relatives. 
</P>
<P>
Another Cessna 172 and its pilot, Jerry Dell Teel, 48, of San Bernardino, were 
found by hikers at nearly 12,000 feet in Sequoia National Park, deputies said. 
Teel's plane disappeared during a heavy snowstorm in January, and a weeklong 
search failed to locate the craft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
