<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INDEPENDENCE BANK SHOWS PROFIT IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Independence Bank in Encino reported a net income of $1.33 million for the 
second quarter that ended June 30, compared to a loss of $256,000 a year 
earlier. For the first six months of 1990, Independence's profit about tripled 
to $2.79 million from $922,000 last year. 
</P>
<P>
On June 30 the bank had assets of $718 million, an increase of 14% from $629 
million a year ago. 
