<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
APARTMENT INTRUDER ATTACKS WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT LAIT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Irvine woman was attacked Monday by a man who broke into her apartment, 
threatened her with a pair of scissors and demanded money, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The 36-year-old woman, whose name was not released, received minor injuries 
during the 5:40 a.m. incident, Police Sgt. Dave Frew said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman apparently awoke after hearing noises in her apartment in the 300 
block of Berkeley Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
When she went into another room to investigate, "the suspect confronted (her) 
with a pair of scissors and forced her back into the bedroom," Frew said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect demanded money and fled, Frew said. The sergeant was uncertain 
whether the suspect got away with any money. MATT LAIT 
</P>
</TEXT>
