<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUKES TRY TO END SKID AGAINST HEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Newport Beach Dukes will try to end a two-match losing streak when they 
play host to the Charlotte Heat at 7:30 tonight in a Team Tennis match at the 
John Wayne Tennis Club. 
</P>
<P>
The Dukes lost consecutive matches to the Los Angeles Strings Friday and 
Saturday. Trevor Kronemann, a four-time all-American at UC Irvine under Dukes 
Coach Greg Patton, is a member of the Heat. 
</P>
<P>
A volleyball exhibition with Olympic gold medalist Randy Stoklos that was 
scheduled during a break in tonight's tennis action has been cancelled. 
</P>
