<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Library Computers: The Richard Nixon Library and Birthplace in Yorba Linda has 
purchased personal computers for its archives and offices from AST Research 
Inc., the Irvine-based maker of computer systems said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The AST systems will assist the library in recording and updating all materials 
received from the National Archives in Washington. 
</P>
