<TEXT>
<P>
Camarena trial -- A story in Friday's editions incorrectly reported that two 
government witnesses, Hector Cervantes Santos and Enrique Plascencia Aguilar, 
had testified that they had seen Honduran drug kingpin Juan Ramon Matta 
Ballesteros at 1984 meetings where the kidnaping of U.S. Drug Enforcement 
Administration agent Enrique Camarena was discussed. In fact, only Cervantes 
testified that he had seen Matta at the meetings. 
