P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
XEROX EARNINGS DECLINE 27% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STAMFORD, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xerox Corp. today reported a 27% drop in second-quarter earnings, blaming 
declines in its insurance business. 
</P>
<P>
For the second quarter, after-tax profit totaled $130 million, or $1.16 per 
share, compared with $179 million, or $1.67 per share, a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue edged up 2.3%, to $4.5 billion from $4.4 billion a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Second-quarter revenue from insurance and other financial services was $1.2 
billion, down 4% from $1.3 billion a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Income from document processing, the company's core business, was $128 million 
in the second quarter, a 5% increase from the 1989 level of $123 million. 
Revenue increased 6%, to $3.3 billion from $3.1 billion in the second quarter 
of 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
