</P>
<P>
LINDA BLAIR SEES NEW DEMONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FROM TIMES WIRE SERVICES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Linda Blair is back and she says the country needs to exorcise a few 
demons. "What irks me is the street gangs who roam around beating up on 
people," she told the New York Daily News. 
</P>
<P>
"I would put them all in a box and ship them off to one of the Eastern European 
countries, where they would learn how good it is to be an American," said 
Blair, who starred as the poor, possessed waif in the 1973 movie "The 
Exorcist." She isn't so sure, however, about how to handle the homeless 
population. 
</P>
<P>
"We've got to do something about them," she said. "I don't know what -- but 
anything." Blair co-stars in an upcoming spoof of "The Exorcist" titled 
"Repossessed," in which the devil once again takes control of her. 
</P>
